@waterlx  I would +1 on your proposal of some serializable table interface. I understand @rdblue argument on not making `Table` interface serializable. 

We defined a holder interface that holds the serializable components/fields/properties from the `Table` interface in our internal PoC implementation of Flink Iceberg source. However, I don't like the interface name `TableProperties` as it can easily get confused with the table properties concept in Iceberg.
```
import lombok.Value;

@Value
public class TableProperties implements Serializable {

  private final Schema schema;
  private final FileIO fileIO;
  private final EncryptionManager encryptionManager;

  public TableProperties(Table table) {
    this.schema = table.schema();
    this.fileIO = table.io();
    this.encryptionManager = table.encryption();
  }
}
```

